description.text:
Made a few of these single Hand coat racks over the years for people.  They keep breaking so I decided it was time for a little REMIX!!!  Used MeshMixer to create a dual helping hands coat rack.  Added counterbored holes in the back so that the hands could be reinforced with a M3x40 bolt and washer or any size bolt you can get to fit in there.  
Also wanted to see what customizer was all about so I spent half a Saturday figuring out how to create 3D models based on code.  It can make you dizzy, but getting the hang of it wasn't too bad.  Now after all of that...  You can create a coat rack with your own name on it.  Enjoy!!!
